`withdraw` sends ETH before zeroing `balances[msg.sender]`. During the external call, the attacker's contract can call `transfer` (not `withdraw` again) — `transfer` reads `balances[msg.sender]` which is still the original value (not yet zeroed), so the attacker can transfer their full original balance to another address *while also* receiving the ETH. When `balances[msg.sender] = 0` finally executes, the transferred funds are unaffected.

